KB how to create a MAIN branch with different name then MASTER:

1. create a new repo without any file or branches
2. clone that repo to your local
3. change directory to the newly cloned repository
4. create a new file: readme.txt
5. git add readme.txt
6. git commit -m "first file"
7. git branch -m master different-master-branch-name
8. git push origin different-master-branch-name

notice that the new branch created is MAIN and has the name you specificed (different-master-branch-name)
